# Project Structure Guide

This is a Ghibli-style image generator built with Next.js and TypeScript. The application allows users to upload images and transform them into Studio Ghibli inspired artwork using AI.

## Key Files and Directories

### Main Application Files
- [pages/index.tsx](mdc:pages/index.tsx) - The main landing page with image upload and transformation functionality
- [pages/_app.tsx](mdc:pages/_app.tsx) - Next.js application entry point
- [pages/my-gallery.tsx](mdc:pages/my-gallery.tsx) - Gallery page for user-generated images

### Components
- [components/ImageUploader.tsx](mdc:components/ImageUploader.tsx) - Handles image upload functionality
- [components/QuotaDisplay.tsx](mdc:components/QuotaDisplay.tsx) - Displays user's remaining generation quota
- [components/SubscriptionModal.tsx](mdc:components/SubscriptionModal.tsx) - Modal for purchasing generation credits
- [components/TotoroLoader.tsx](mdc:components/TotoroLoader.tsx) - Loading animation during image generation
- [components/Layout.tsx](mdc:components/Layout.tsx) - Main layout wrapper

### Internationalization
- [locales/en/common.json](mdc:locales/en/common.json) - English translations
- [locales/zh/common.json](mdc:locales/zh/common.json) - Chinese translations
- [next-i18next.config.js](mdc:next-i18next.config.js) - i18n configuration

### Configuration
- [next.config.js](mdc:next.config.js) - Next.js configuration
- [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js) - Tailwind CSS configuration
